article.headline: Navy 57, Lafayette 52
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- Jordan Sugars scored 17 points and Navy held off a second-half rally by Lafayette in a 57-52 win Saturday night. The Midshipmen (9-17, 4-6 Patriot League) led by as many as 17, 38-21, early in the second half. Navy was then outscored 31-16 over the next 16:43 as Lafayette cut it to two, 54-52, on Tony Johnson's layup. The Leopards (10-15, 5-5) had a chance to tie it after Rob Delaney's steal, but Jim Mower missed a layup with 22 seconds left. Navy's O.J. Avoworo made 1 of 2 free throws with 20 seconds remaining, and made two more 10 seconds later to seal it. The Midshipmen, ranked last in the country in rebounding margin (minus-11.7), outrebounded Lafayette 34-32. They had been outrebounded by at least 20 in each of their previous three games and have lost the battle of the boards to 33 of its past 36 Division I foes. Jared Mintz led Lafayette with 17 points.
